File: ex2a.cc
Obtaining the result of how many numbers are even, odd, positive,zero and negative
========================================
Writen by: Eliane Dahab

This program identifies the numbers according to their classification.

Compile: g++ -Wall ex2a.cc –o ex2a
Run: ex2a
Input: Four random numbers for the identification of how many of them are even, odd, positive, zero and negative
e.g. 45 60 -23 0 for the identification of even, odd, positive, zero and negative

Output: 2 2
2 1 1
Meaning that 2 numbers are even including zero as even, 2 number are odd, 2 number are positive, there is one zero and one negative number.

File: ex2b.cc
Getting the greater value between 3 number with sum and multiplication operations
========================================
Writen by: Eliane Dahab, id = 338038839, login = elianech

This program obtain the maximum result between 3 numbers with sum and multiplication operations.

Compile: g++ -Wall ex2b.cc –o ex2b
Run: ex2b
Input: Three random numbers for the operations of sum and multiplication
e.g., 9 12 -3

Output: 12 \* 9 + (-3) = 105

File: ex2c.cc
Getting the date in numbers and putting in words
========================================
Writen by: Eliane Dahab, id = 338038839, login = elianech

This program convert any date puted in number to words

Compile: g++ -Wall ex2c.cc –o ex2c
Run: ex2c
Input: Any date in numbers
e.g., 18 6 1989

Output: 18th June 1989
